‘Cybele spoke in anger; her hands drew back the yoke, and the monster, summoning his might, sprang furiously forward. Blind with terror he fied · into the fastnesses of the forest, and there remained in bondage for ever, until he died.

Great goddess, goddess Cybele, goddess and queen of Dindy- mus! Grant, dear mistress, that thy sever may never light upon my house: choose others for that headlong rout, drive others on that passionate pilgrimage.⁷
